<script type="application/json" data-for="htmlwidget-cee3bf1bdb656af1da55">{"x":{"filter":"none","vertical":false,"data":[["Creation of study protocol & funding proposal                      ","Creation of study protocol & funding proposal                      ","Creation of study protocol & funding proposal                      ","Creation of informed consent process and informed consentform (ICF)","Creation of questionnaires and other study tools                   ","Creation of questionnaires and other study tools                   "],["One PPI representative co-creates or reviews          ","A group of PPI representatives co-create or review    ","PPI representatives provide a formal letter of support","NA                                                    ","A group of PPI representatives co-create and review   ","A group of PPI representatives co-create and review   "],["A Protocol Advisor was involved. The Protocol Advisor, living with HIV and part of the military HIV programme, made suggestions and recommendations based on personal experiences and knowledge. He provided important feedback from the perspective of the patient with issues specific and not-so-specific to the military, issues regarding confidentiality, sexuality, drug and alcohol use, and the difference between military duties and responsibilities throughout the protocol stages.","Working group members facilitated workshops with youth to train them in research methods and collaboratively designed the protocol. In all, 27 youth participated in an iterative protocol planning process.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    ","PPI representatives wrote a letter of support for a project funding proposal                                                                    